.Dd April 18, 2026
.Dt PROWLD 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm prowld
.Nd MidnightBSD service management daemon
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl d
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a dependency-aware, parallel-execution service manager for MidnightBSD.
It supersedes the traditional sequential
.Xr rc 8
startup model while maintaining full backward compatibility with existing
.Pa /etc/rc.d
scripts and the
.Xr service 8
command.
.Pp
.Nm
reads unit files from several directories, wraps legacy
.Xr rc.d 8
scripts as compatibility shims, builds a dependency graph, and starts
services in parallel based on dependency ordering.
.Pp
The following option is available:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl d
Debug mode.
.Nm
runs in the foreground and writes log messages to standard error in
addition to
.Xr syslog 3 .
.El
.Sh UNIT FILES
Unit files are parsed by
.Xr libucl 3
and accept UCL, JSON, or simplified YAML syntax.
Files must have the
.Pa .unit
extension.
.Pp
Unit file directories are searched in the following order (later overrides
earlier):
.Bl -enum -compact
.It
.Pa /etc/prowld/units.d/
.It
.Pa /usr/local/etc/prowld/units.d/
.It
.Pa /etc/prowld/overrides.d/
.It
.Pa /var/run/prowld/generated.d/
.El
.Pp
A minimal unit file:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "label": "org.midnightbsd.sshd",
  "description": "OpenSSH Daemon",
  "program": "/usr/sbin/sshd",
  "arguments": ["-D"],
  "run_at_load": true,
  "keep_alive": true
}
.Ed
.Ss Required Fields
.Bl -tag -width "label"
.It Va label
Unique reverse-DNS identifier for the job
(e.g., \fBorg.midnightbsd.sshd\fR).
.It Va program
Path to the executable.
Required unless
.Va arguments[0]
is a full path.
.El
.Ss Identity Fields
.Bl -tag -width "description"
.It Va description
Human-readable description string.
.It Va type
One of
.Cm daemon ,
.Cm oneshot ,
.Cm timer ,
.Cm socket .
Default:
.Cm daemon .
.It Va rc_name
Variable prefix used in
.Pa rc.conf
for the
.Va _enable
flag.
Defaults to the last dot-separated component of
.Va label .
.El
.Ss Execution Fields
.Bl -tag -width "working_directory"
.It Va arguments
Array of strings passed as
.Vt argv .
.It Va environment
Object of key/value pairs added to the process environment.
.It Va working_directory
Directory to
.Xr chdir 2
into before starting the program.
.It Va root_directory
Optional
.Xr chroot 2
target.
.It Va user , Va group
Drop privileges to this user and group before starting.
.It Va umask
Octal umask string (e.g.,
.Dq 0022 ) .
.El
.Ss Lifecycle Fields
.Bl -tag -width "throttle_interval"
.It Va run_at_load
If true, start the job automatically when it is loaded and all
dependencies are satisfied.
.It Va keep_alive
Boolean or object controlling restart policy.
Object keys:
.Va always ,
.Va crashed ,
.Va successful_exit .
.It Va throttle_interval
Minimum seconds between restart attempts.
Default: 10.
.It Va exit_timeout
Seconds to wait after
.Dv SIGTERM
before sending
.Dv SIGKILL .
Default: 20.
.El
.Ss Dependency Fields
.Bl -tag -width "conflicts"
.It Va requires
Array of capability names that must be running before this job starts.
Failure of a required dependency causes this job to fail.
.It Va wants
Like
.Va requires ,
but failure of the dependency does not fail this job.
.It Va before
This job must start before the listed jobs.
.It Va after
This job must start after the listed jobs.
.It Va conflicts
Jobs that cannot run while this job is running.
Starting this job stops the listed jobs.
.It Va provides
Array of capability names this job satisfies.
.El
.Ss I/O Fields
.Bl -tag -width "standard_error_path"
.It Va standard_in_path
Path for standard input.
Defaults to
.Pa /dev/null .
.It Va standard_out_path
Path for standard output.
.It Va standard_error_path
Path for standard error.
.El
.Ss Notification Fields
.Bl -tag -width "notify_type"
.It Va notify_type
.Cm none
(default) or
.Cm notify
(sd_notify-compatible).
.It Va watchdog_sec
Watchdog interval in seconds.
0 disables the watchdog.
.El
.Sh BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY
All existing scripts in
.Pa /etc/rc.d
and
.Pa /usr/local/etc/rc.d
are automatically discovered and wrapped as compatibility shim jobs.
The
.Dv REQUIRE ,
.Dv PROVIDE ,
.Dv BEFORE ,
and
.Dv KEYWORD
headers are parsed and translated into
.Nm
dependency fields.
.Pp
Enable state is read from
.Pa /etc/rc.conf
using the
.Va <name>_enable
variable, exactly as
.Xr rc.subr 8
does.
.Pp
If a native unit file and an
.Pa rc.d
script both claim the same
.Va provides ,
the native unit wins and the
.Pa rc.d
script is skipped.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/var/run/prowld/prowld.sock" -compact
.It Pa /etc/prowld/prowld.conf
Daemon configuration file.
.It Pa /etc/prowld/units.d/
Base system unit files.
.It Pa /usr/local/etc/prowld/units.d/
Ports and packages unit files.
.It Pa /etc/prowld/overrides.d/
Local administrator overrides.
.It Pa /var/run/prowld/prowld.sock
Control socket (Unix domain, mode 0660, owned root:wheel).
.It Pa /var/run/prowld/prowld.pid
PID file.
.It Pa /var/db/prowld/masked.d/
Symlinks to
.Pa /dev/null
for masked services.
.It Pa /etc/rc.conf
Authoritative source for service enable state.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr prowlctl 8 ,
.Xr rc 8 ,
.Xr rc.conf 5 ,
.Xr rcorder 8 ,
.Xr service 8 ,
.Xr sysrc 8
.Sh HISTORY
.Nm
first appeared in MidnightBSD 4.1.
